### POST /v2/idp_intents

Source: https://zitadel.com/docs/guides/integrate/login-ui/external-login

Initiates the authentication flow with an external identity provider.

```APIDOC
## POST /v2/idp_intents

### Description
Initiates the authentication flow with a configured external identity provider. Returns an authentication URL to redirect the user.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
https://${CUSTOM_DOMAIN}/v2/idp_intents

### Request Body
- **idpId** (string) - Required - The ID of the identity provider.
- **urls** (object) - Required - Contains successUrl and failureUrl.

### Request Example
{
  "idpId": "$IDP_ID",
  "urls": {
    "successUrl": "https://custom.com/login/idp/success",
    "failureUrl": "https://custom.com/login/idp/fail"
  }
}

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **details** (object) - Metadata about the intent creation.
- **authUrl** (string) - The URL to redirect the user to for external authentication.

#### Response Example
{
	"details": {
		"sequence": "592",
		"changeDate": "2023-06-14T12:51:29.654819Z",
		"resourceOwner": "163840776835432705"
	},
	"authUrl": "https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/v2/auth?..."
}
```

--------------------------------

### Create Session for Passkey Login

Source: https://zitadel.com/docs/guides/integrate/login-ui/passkey

Initiate a session with ZITADEL to receive the necessary WebAuthN challenge options.

```bash
curl --request POST \
  --url https://${CUSTOM_DOMAIN}/v2/sessions \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer '"$TOKEN"''\
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{
  "checks": {
    "user": {
      "loginName": "minni-mouse@mouse.com"
    }
  },
  "metadata": {},
  "challenges": {
    "webAuthN": {
      "domain": "example.domain.com",
      "userVerificationRequirement": "USER_VERIFICATION_REQUIREMENT_REQUIRED"
    }
  }
}'
```

```json
{
  "details": {
    "sequence": "2",
    "changeDate": "2023-06-27",
    "resourceOwner": "69629023906488334"
  },
  "sessionId": "d654e6ba-70a3-48ef-a95d-37c8d8a7901a",
  "sessionToken": "string",
  "challenges": {
    "webAuthN": {
      "publicKeyCredentialRequestOptions": {
        "publicKey": {
          "allowCredentials": [
            {
              "id": "REDACTED",
              "type": "public-key"
            }
          ],
          "challenge": "REDACTED",
          "rpId": "example.domain.com",
          "timeout": 300000,
          "userVerification": "required"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Authenticate Passkey in Browser

Source: https://zitadel.com/docs/guides/integrate/login-ui/passkey

Use the browser's WebAuthN API to retrieve credentials for authentication using the challenge options from ZITADEL.

```javascript
const credential = await navigator.credentials.get({
    publicKey: publicKeyCredentialRequestOptions
});
```

--------------------------------

### Register Passkey in Browser

Source: https://zitadel.com/docs/guides/integrate/login-ui/passkey

Call the browser's WebAuthN API to create a new credential using options provided by ZITADEL.

```javascript
const credential = await navigator.credentials.create({
    publicKey: publicKeyCredentialCreationOptions
});
```

### Configure Social Logins > Google

Source: https://zitadel.com/docs/guides/integrate/identity-providers/apple

ZITADEL supports configuring Google as an external identity provider for social login. This allows users to authenticate using their Google accounts.

